Hi

If anyone is interested, there's a nice perl script similar to l'edit, but 
for Lisp:  http://vim.sourceforge.net/scripts/script.php?script_id=221
It adds readline to the input interface and also it creates a pipe, so one 
can also interact with the Lisp interpreter from VIM instead of readline.

(Like myself, the author hated Emacs)

